<br>
We live our lives in cycles, and the year governs one of the strongest ones.  Holidays, special events, birthdays, family gatherings, we live in the cycle of the seasons, and with each passing season during the year of grief, we learn to experience all those things again, both in the sadness of the loss we feel that someone is no longer there, and in the new light of understanding of how important each moment, each day, each year is.<br>
<br>
Do not embrace your grief such that you exclude the rest of your life, or push it away from you and hide it in the dark.  Accept it, live, live *twice*, grab on.  It's what we have. <br>
